        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 13 at 6:34AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>An area of light snow will continue to impact the I15 corridor
Between Hardy Creek and Boulder Hill and highway 287 along
Canyon Ferry Lake. Accumulations will generally remain around an
inch or less, with some slushy roadway accumulation possible. The
snow is expected to diminish over the next hour or so.

Anyone traveling this morning may encounter wet, or even slushy
roads and reduced visibility below one mile at times. Slow down
and allow extra time to reach your destination.
</description>
